.TH "kmemleak_scan_area" 9 "kmemleak_scan_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kmemleak_scan_area \- limit the range to be scanned in an allocated object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __ref" kmemleak_scan_area
.BI "(const void *ptr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ptr" 12
pointer to beginning or inside the object. This also
represents the start of the scan area
.IP "size" 12
size of the scan area
.IP "gfp" 12
\fBkmalloc\fP flags used for kmemleak internal memory allocations
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used when it is known that only certain parts of an object
contain references to other objects. Kmemleak will only scan these areas
reducing the number false negatives.
